{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''''Authenticité''''' was the name given to the [[Chad]]ian president [[François (Ngarta) Tombalbaye]]'s attempt to remove foreign influence and promote southern Chadian culture throughout Chad during the 1970s. One of its most unpopular requirements was that [[civil servant]]s underwent the ''yondo'' [[initiation rite]]s common only amongst Tombalbaye's own subgroup of [[Sara people]] in southern Chad.

A similar concept, also called ''[[Authenticité (Zaire)|authenticité]]'', was introduced by [[Mobutu Sese Seko]] in [[Zaïre]].

